>Is this new, though? Surely all teenagers since the dawn of time have been obsessed with sex.</strong> Well, yes. But, still, forewarned is forearmed.</p> <p><strong>Go on then, give me another example. </strong>Have you ever seen your kid write “POS” on their WhatsApp?</p> <p><strong>No, because I think my child is more likely to appropriately self-police if I’m not constantly snooping on them. </strong>Parent Over Shoulder, that’s what it means. It means they can’t talk about sex and drugs because you’re around. What about IWSN?</p> <aside class=\"element element-rich-link element--thumbnail\"> <p> <span>Related: </span><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/sep/07/teen-chat-kpc-tmi-imho\">In the world of teen chat KPC is better than TMI, IMHO | Suzanne Moore</a> </p> </aside>  <p><strong>Fine, whatever, tell me.</strong> I Want Sex Now. That’s what it means.</p> <p><strong>Of course they want sex now. They’re teenagers. I wanted sex now when I was a teenager but it didn’t mean I ever got it.</strong> Yuck, TMI.</p> <p><strong>Do say:</strong> “KIAPBWATS – Knowledge is a parent’s best weapon against teenage sex.”</p> <p><strong>Don’t say:</strong> “TIAPNA – This is all probably nonsense actually.”</p>","internalOctopusCode":"10754590","productionOffice":"UK","newspaperEditionDate":"2015-09-08T00:00:00Z","hasStoryPackage":"false","internalPageCode":"2366948","internalRevision":"65","internalContentCode":"457883201","publication":"The Guardian","trailText":"The government has just launched a website to help parents work out what their kids are up to online – although you may not be that surprised","allowUgc":"false","headline":"MOOS, POS and other teen internet slang every parent urgently needs to know","isInappropriateForSponsorship":"false","commentable":"true","firstPublicationDate":"2015-09-07T14:18:03Z","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/9/7/1441634180381/TL---POS---TTFN.-001.jpg","isPremoderated":"fals