honda-rhimes\" title=\"\">air the new Muppets TV show in the US later this month</a> – plus she’s a pig.</p> <p><strong>Wow, Kermit really has a type, doesn’t he?</strong> Only in that Denise and Miss Piggy are both pigs. They will be truly similar only if Denise suddenly becomes a dangerous egotist and starts beating up Kermit for kicks.</p> <p><strong>And how has Miss Piggy taken this news? </strong>Well, the actor Liam Hemsworth recently <a href=\"https://instagram.com/liamhemsworth/\" title=\"\">posted an Instagram shot</a> where he is gazing adoringly into her eyes, so maybe that says something.</p> <p><strong>He certainly seems like a step up from Kermit.</strong> Does he? What if they have children? Is the idea of a tiny, squealing, deformed pig-human hybrid really any less horrific than the idea of a tiny, squealing, deformed frog-pig hybrid?</p> <p><strong>I can’t say I’ve given it any thought.</strong> Well, do it. Give it some thought.</p> <p><strong>OK, I think a pig-man is probably slightly worse than a frog-pig.</strong> So what you’re saying is that you want Kermit and Miss Piggy to get back together?</p> <p><strong>I think so. </strong>You’re a terrible person. Also, you’re in luck because the Kermit-Piggy relationship will probably be central to the new Muppets show, or else ABC wouldn’t be busting a gut trying to sell a non-starter like Denise to us. Also, the Muppets are fictional and none of this matters.</p> <p><strong>Do say: </strong>“Please welcome Denise to the Muppet family!”</p> <p><strong>Don’t say:</strong> “Remember <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mildred_Huxtetter\" title=\"\">Mildred Huxtetter</a>?”</p>","internalOctopusCode":"10738400","productionOffice":"UK","newspaperEditionDate":"2015-09-03T00:00:00Z","hasStoryPackage":"false","internalPageCode":"2364313","internalContentCode":"457850598","internalRevision":"28","publication":"The Guardian","trailText":"In the new Muppets TV show, the gaze of the world’s favourite frog – a