be whether she should endorse small kitchen appliances for a <a href=\"http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/08/30/how-low-can-fergie-go-the-duchess-of-york-is-sell-sell-sell.html\">QVC infomercial</a>.</p> <p><strong>That is a major concern? </strong>She <a href=\"http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/life/celebrity/article4323792.ece\">credits</a> Tristar’s Fusion Xcelerator food emulsifier with her recent 25kg (55lb) weight loss and highlights other Tristar products on her website under the heading “Duchess Discoveries”.</p> <p><strong>Ah, I can practically hear Prince Philip jackknifing in pain in a picture gallery somewhere. </strong>They include a set of hairstyling tongs.</p> <p><strong>He’s just fallen to the floor, fibrillating. I hope someone passes by soon. </strong>Last year it was suggested that she was going to launch a range of pudding-flavoured teas.</p> <p><strong>It’s a fabulously indiscriminate work ethic she’s got, isn’t it? </strong>Like an unremitting series of lunges after random lump sums.</p> <p><strong>No wonder she’s losing weight. </strong>And no wonder the Americans love her and the British aristos sneer.</p> <p><strong>Nicely played, Sarah F, nicely played. </strong>The duchess is her own greatest discovery.</p> <p><strong>Do say:</strong> Tremendous!</p> <p><strong>Don’t say:</strong> This blender costs £60. Duchess, you are having a laugh.</p>","internalOctopusCode":"10732192","productionOffice":"UK","newspaperEditionDate":"2015-09-01T00:00:00Z","hasStoryPackage":"false","internalPageCode":"2362979","internalContentCode":"457834713","internalRevision":"67","publication":"The Guardian","trailText":"Fergie is back, flogging blenders on QVC and no doubt causing consternation in Buck House","allowUgc":"false","headline":"Sarah Ferguson’s busy summer: shopping channels and Swiss chalets","isInappropriateForSponsorship":"false","commentable":"true","firstPublicationDate":"2015-08-31T15:33:23.039+01:00","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys